Brownies get better with age, so always try to INGREDIENTS
make them a day ahead. Let them cool 125g unsalted butter, chopped
completely in the pan – they are very soft when 125g dark chocolate, chopped
hot and can break easily.
3 eggs, lightly whisked
335g (1 1/2 cups) CSR White Sugar
115g (3/4 cup) plain our
30g (1/4 cup) Dutch cocoa powder
1 teaspoon vanilla extract
Pinch of salt
EQUIPMENT
20cm (base measurement) square cake
pan

METHOD

Step 1
Preheat oven to 180C/160C fan forced. Grease a 20cm (base measurement) square cake pan and line with
baking paper.

Step 2
Place butter and chocolate in a heatproof bowl over a saucepan of simmering water (don't let the bowl touch
the water). Stir with a metal spoon until melted. Remove from heat. Quickly stir in egg, sugar, �our, cocoa
powder, vanilla and salt until just combined. Pour into prepared pan. Bake for 30 minutes or until a skewer
inserted in the centre comes out with moist crumbs clinging. Set aside to cool completely.